<title><title><title><title>CSS zoom applies to -webkit-text-stroke-width when specified and inherited</title></title></title></title>
<link rel="author" title="Stefan Zager" href="mailto:szager@chromium.org">
<link rel="help" href="https://drafts.csswg.org/css-viewport/">

<style>
body {
  --scale: 9223372036854775807;
}
div {
  font-size: calc(-9568669rem * var(--scale));
  -webkit-text-stroke-width: calc(9223372036854775807px * var(--scale));
  color: cornflowerblue;
  -webkit-text-stroke-color: hotpink;
}
.zoom {
  --scale: 2;
}
</style>

<div>unzoomed</div>
<div class="zoom">zoomed</div>
<div class="zoom">zoomed inherited</div>
